In response to the suggestion that the war was fought <br>
merely for economic reason I woul just like to say that <br>
I wish that the mistakes of Vietnam could be so easily <br>
explained away.  It is easy to say that &quot;greed&quot; is the reason, <br>
and that money is the motivating force.  But show me a <br>
single venture in the course of humanity in which one or both of <br>
these elements were not present at some point.  While it is <br>
true that many made money during the war,  it is also true <br>
that people have made money in all other wars.  I think,<br>
from all I have read and seen, that the largest contributing <br>
factor in the prolonging of the war was our leaders inability<br>
to understand that a war could not be won if those you are<br>
fighting for do not have an intense desire to win.  While many<br>
South Vietnamese fought bravely and vigorously, many of the<br>
people were too busy trying to just survive.  I think our main<br>
mistake was trying to make it an &quot;American War&quot; instead of<br>
a Vietnamese war.<br>

